text_Original: A kicker is that they do NOT include the hands (you will notice them using hands in the VIDEO, but no output in the avatars). One would think they would focus on using the Hand Tracking tech on device to try and render the hands (at least on a BASIC way, not hyper-realistic). Gesticulation and 'speaking with hands' really helps with communication for some. Love the detailed fidelity, but black-void shows that the processing tech may not be there in the Quest Pro (still on XR1, not the XR2 like the Quest 3). Not sure, but definitely interesting.
